  "prompt": "Why isn't the top answer on Quora the most upvoted one?",
  "response": "Quora's algorithm for determining the order of answers is more complex than simply showing the most upvoted answer at the top. While upvotes are an important factor, Quora also considers other elements such as the relevance of the answer to the question, the credibility and expertise of the person providing the answer, and the engagement the answer receives (e.g., comments, shares).\n\nAdditionally, Quora aims to provide a personalized experience for its users. This means that the order of answers might be different for different users based on their previous interactions, interests, and the people they follow on the platform.\n\nIn some cases, Quora may also promote answers from its knowledge program or from verified accounts to ensure that high-quality, well-researched information is easily accessible to users.\n\nOverall, while the number of upvotes is a significant factor in determining the order of answers on Quora, it is not the only one, which is why the most upvoted answer may not always appear at the top.",
